TY  - JOUR
AU  - Driessen, Joost
T1  - Is Default Event Risk Priced in Corporate Bonds?
PY  - 2005
Y1  - 2005/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhi009
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 18
IS  - 1
SP  - 165
EP  - 195
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article provides an empirical decomposition of the default, liquidity, and tax factors that determine expected corporate bond returns. In particular, the risk premium associated with a default event is estimated. The intensity-based model is estimated using bond price data for 104 US firms and historical default rates. Significant risk premia on common intensity factors and important tax and liquidity effects are found. These components go a long way towards explaining the level of expected corporate bond returns. Adding a positive default event risk premium helps to explain the remaining error, although this premium cannot be estimated with high statistical precision.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhi009
ER  - 



