TY  - JOUR
AU  - Yao, Rui
AU  - Zhang, Harold H.
T1  - Optimal Consumption and Portfolio Choices with Risky Housing and Borrowing Constraints
PY  - 2005
Y1  - 2005/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhh007
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 18
IS  - 1
SP  - 197
EP  - 239
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We examine the optimal dynamic portfolio decisions for investors who acquire housing services from either renting or owning a house. Our results show that when indifferent between owning and renting, investors owning a house hold a lower equity proportion in their net worth (bonds, stocks, and home equity), reflecting the substitution effect, yet hold a higher equity proportion in their liquid portfolios (bonds and stocks), reflecting the diversification effect. Furthermore, following the suboptimal policy of always renting leads investors to overweigh in stocks, while following the suboptimal policy of always owning a house causes investors to underweigh in stocks.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhh007
ER  - 



